---
// HeroCaseStudies — the homepage centerpiece. One sentence carries the program's
// three case studies. Hover (or focus) a highlighted word: it lights up as a
// block and a bubble preview of its case study floats in; click to open the
// project. Compounds -> HanGL, modals -> MODUS (the thesis), generics -> ORDO.
// Pure CSS, no underlines.
---

<figure class="hero-cs" aria-label="The example sentence “A schoolteacher must know that birds fly.” Three words are highlighted: schoolteacher (a compound, HanGL), must (a modal, the MODUS thesis), and birds (a generic, ORDO). Hover a word to preview its case study.">
  <p class="hero-cs-sent"><span class="hcs-quote hcs-quote-open" aria-hidden="true">“</span>A <a class="cw cw-c" href="/research/hangl" aria-label="schoolteacher, a compound, HanGL"><span class="cw-word">schoolteacher</span><span class="cw-tip" aria-hidden="true"><span class="tip-cat">Compounds</span><span class="tip-name">HanGL</span><span class="tip-q">Is a word's meaning composed from its morphemes, or memorized as a whole? The morphology case, on Sino-Korean.</span></span></a> <a class="cw cw-m" href="/research/modus" aria-label="must, a modal, the MODUS thesis"><span class="cw-word">must</span><span class="cw-tip" aria-hidden="true"><span class="tip-cat">Modals</span><span class="tip-name">MODUS, the thesis</span><span class="tip-q">Is modal force a set of possible worlds, or a degree of certainty? And does a model represent it, or ride the word?</span></span></a> know that <a class="cw cw-g" href="/research/ordo" aria-label="birds, a generic, ORDO"><span class="cw-word">birds</span><span class="cw-tip" aria-hidden="true"><span class="tip-cat">Generics</span><span class="tip-name">ORDO</span><span class="tip-q">“Birds fly”, except penguins. A default-with-exceptions is an inference classical logic cannot state.</span></span></a> fly.<span class="hcs-quote hcs-quote-close" aria-hidden="true">”</span></p>

  <figcaption class="hero-cs-cap">Three words, three case studies. Hover a word, or click to open it.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .hero-cs { margin: 0; padding: 0; max-width: 32rem; }
  .hero-cs-sent {
    font-family: var(--font-display, serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 1.2rem + 2vw, 2.35rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* big decorative quotes framing the example */
  .hcs-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-display, Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 2.4em;
    line-height: 0;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text-dim) 55%, transparent);
  }
  .hcs-quote-open { margin-right: 0.04em; vertical-align: -0.42em; }
  .hcs-quote-close { margin-left: 0.03em; vertical-align: -0.42em; }

  .cw {
    position: relative;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 1px 4px;
    transition: background 0.14s ease;
  }
  .cw-c { color: var(--accent-teal-deep); }
  .cw-m { color: var(--accent-deep-purple); }
  .cw-g { color: var(--accent-coral); }
  .cw:focus-visible { outline: none; }
  .cw-c:hover, .cw-c:focus-visible { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-teal-deep) 15%, transparent); }
  .cw-m:hover, .cw-m:focus-visible { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 15%, transparent); }
  .cw-g:hover, .cw-g:focus-visible { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-coral) 15%, transparent); }

  /* the bubble preview */
  .cw-tip {
    position: absolute;
    top: calc(100% + 11px);
    left: 0;
    width: max-content;
    max-width: min(300px, 78vw);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.11);
    padding: 0.8rem 0.95rem;
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    transition: opacity 0.16s ease, transform 0.16s ease, visibility 0.16s;
    z-index: 5;
    font-family: var(--font-sans, sans-serif);
  }
  .cw-g .cw-tip { left: auto; right: 0; }
  .cw:hover .cw-tip, .cw:focus-within .cw-tip { opacity: 1; visibility: visible; transform: translateY(0); }
  .cw-tip::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 100%;
    left: 20px;
    border: 6px solid transparent;
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-border);
  }
  .cw-g .cw-tip::before { left: auto; right: 20px; }

  .tip-cat {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }
  .cw-c .tip-cat { color: var(--accent-teal-deep); }
  .cw-m .tip-cat { color: var(--accent-deep-purple); }
  .cw-g .tip-cat { color: var(--accent-coral); }
  .tip-name { display: block; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 5px; }
  .tip-q { display: block; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--color-text-muted); }

  .hero-cs-cap {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    font-size: 11.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }
</style>
